e": "B-unstable", "color": "d304cb", "default": false, "description": "Implemented in the nightly compiler and unstable."}, {"id": 650846969, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA4NDY5Njk=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-tracking-issue", "name": "C-tracking-issue", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A tracking issue for an RFC or an unstable feature."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 33, "created_at": "2015-08-13T00:27:54Z", "updated_at": "2019-04-14T01:11:12Z", "closed_at": "2019-04-14T01:11:12Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "We probably don't want to indefinitely have a large number of facade crates which are all unstable, so we should eventually stabilize these crates, fold them back into the standard library, or find a good middle ground in which they can all reside. \r\n\r\nThe current set of crates considered under this issue are:\r\n- `rustc_unicode`\r\n- `libc`\r\n- `collections`\r\n- `alloc`\r\n- `rand`\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**Update 2018-04-05:**\r\n\r\n* `libc` and `rand` have moved to crates.io\r\n* `collections` [was merged](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/42648) into `alloc`\r\n* `rustc_unicode` was renamed to `std_unicode` and [later merged](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/49698) into `core`\r\n\r\nThis leaves only the `alloc` crate still unstable, which with the stable `core` and `std` crates (plus arguably `proc_macro`) form the standard library.\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n**Update 2018-06-19:**\r\n\r\n[RFC 2480](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/2480) proposes stabilizing the `alloc` crate, which would close this issue.", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https://github.com/bors", "followers_ur